FBIS3-13737 "drnes054_n_94010" FBIS-NES-94-054 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Mar 1994 LEBANON New Chairman for Shiite Council Elected NC1803110094 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain in Arabic 1000 GMT 18 Mar 94 NC1803110094 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] The Higher Islamic Shiite Council held a meeting at its temporary headquarters in Tallat al-Khayyat this morning and elected Shaykh Muhammad Mahdi Shams-al-Din council chairman, succeeding Shaykh Musa al-Sar, the council's founder [who disappeared during a visit to Libya in August 1978]. Shaykh Shams-al-Din has been deputy chairman of the council since 1974. The council members also elected Ja'farite Mufti 'Abd-al-Amir Qabalan as first deputy chairman and Dr. 'Adnan Haydar as second deputy chairman. Some 46 of the council's 48 members attended the session. [passage omitted]
